<plot>Bosko and Honey perform a wacky stage act that includes doing imitations of 'Maurice Chevalier (I)' (qv), 'Greta Garbo' (qv) and 'Jimmy Durante' (qv). Singing, dancing and piano playing are the order of the day. Bosko's anthropomorphic glove even gets in on the act by reciting "Mary Had a Little Lamb." If the performance can be said to have a flaw, it's that Bosko gets a little carried away while dancing, making it no surprise when he finally falls off the stage.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?080149</url></doc>
